TypeSignature.Value: .class public interface auto ansi abstract ISymbolWriter

Docs.summary: Represents a symbol writer for managed code.

remarks.format:
## Remarks The <xref:System.Diagnostics.SymbolStore.ISymbolWriter> interface provides methods that define documents, sequence points, lexical scopes, and variables.
> [!NOTE] > This interface is the managed counterpart of the `ISymUnmanagedWriter` interface, which is one of the unmanaged symbol store interfaces that provides an alternative way to read and write debug symbol information.

The start offset for the variable. If this parameter is zero, it is ignored and the variable is defined throughout the entire scope. If the parameter is nonzero, the variable falls within the offsets of the current scope.

The end offset for the variable. If this parameter is zero, it is ignored and the variable is defined throughout the entire scope. If the parameter is nonzero, the variable falls within the offsets of the current scope.
Docs.summary: Defines a single variable in the current lexical scope.

remarks.format:
## Remarks The `startOffset` and `endOffset` parameters are optional. If their value is zero, they are ignored and the variable is defined throughout the entire scope. If their value is nonzero, the variable falls within the offsets of the current scope.
You can call <xref:System.Diagnostics.SymbolStore.ISymbolWriter.DefineLocalVariable%2A> multiple times for a variable of the same name that occurs multiple times in different offset ranges throughout a scope. (In this case, start and end offsets must not overlap.)
